{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778550045,"nonce":"l+Q9hlQyEkg/95dCkZfTLZFrZa0=","title":"train_minimax.py: adversarial_model.eqx save/load fails when n_adversary_batches=0","message":"When `n_adversary_batches=0` (pure-warmup matrices), the training script still saves `adversarial_model.eqx` at the end. The saved file contains adversary state (e.g., `DisturbanceField.params_index.init.amplitude`) whose PyTree shape does not match the local skeleton produced by `setup_task_model_pair` when reconstructing for analysis â€” `eqx.tree_deserialise_leaves` then fails.\n\n## Concrete consequence\n\nEncountered while building `scripts/analyse_lit_replication_6cell.py` (issue `f47abb1`). The matrix had `n_adversary_batches=0`. Loading `adversarial_model.eqx` to inspect trained weights failed; workaround was to load `warmup_model.eqx` instead (same model weights since the adversarial phase did not actually run).\n\n## Fix options\n\n1. **Skip save when no adversarial phase**: in `scripts/train_minimax.py`, if `n_adversary_batches=0`, do NOT write `adversarial_model.eqx`. This is the lightest fix; downstream analysis falls back to `warmup_model.eqx` naturally.\n2. **Save with the local skeleton**: when `n_adversary_batches=0`, serialise using the `setup_task_model_pair`-style skeleton (no populated adversary state). Heavier but preserves the canonical \"post-training output\" filename.\n3. **Make the loader robust**: in analysis scripts, allow `eqx.tree_deserialise_leaves` to tolerate skeleton mismatches via tree-restructuring. Most invasive.\n\nOption (1) is preferred. Option (2) is a viable alternative if there is a reason to always have an `adversarial_model.eqx` artifact.\n\n## Severity\n\n- Low while we are running adversarial training (`n_adversary_batches \u003e 0`): the local skeleton matches the saved file because both come from the same pipeline.\n- Bites every time on pure-warmup matrices (`n_adversary_batches=0`) â€” like the recent `f47abb1` lit-replication run.\n\n## References\n\n- `f47abb1` â€” lit-replication matrix where this was first encountered.\n- `2bc95fd` â€” prior 6-cell matrix; also pure-warmup; may have had the same issue silently (its analysis script used a different load path).\n- `scripts/train_minimax.py` â€” where the unconditional save lives (search for `adversarial_model.eqx`).\n- `scripts/analyse_lit_replication_6cell.py` â€” loader that hit the issue; currently uses warmup_model.eqx workaround.","files":null}]}